quran[8]{c,v,t}:
  5,96,"The game of the sea and its food have been made lawful for you<a class=""sup""><sup>pl </sup></a>as an enjoyment for you and for travelers, while the game of the land has been forbidden for you as long as you are consecrating yourselves to pilgrimage. And be mindful of Allah to whom you are herded."
  5,97,"Allah has appointed the Kaʻbah—the Inviolable House—a leverage for mankind, as well as every inviolable month and the offerings and the garlanded; all this so that you may know that Allah knows whatever is in the heavens and whatever is in the earth, and that Allah is All-Knowing of everything."
  5,98,"Know<a class=""sup""><sup>pl </sup></a>that Allah is Stern in retribution, and that Allah is Oft-Forgiving, Bestowing of mercy."
  5,99,"The Messenger’s only responsibility is proclamation, while Allah knows what you disclose and what you conceal."
  5,100,"Say<a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a>, “The nasty and the good are not equal, even though the multitude of the nasty may impress you<a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a>. So be mindful of Allah, O you people of understanding, that you may succeed.”"
  5,101,"O you who have attained faith, do not ask about things that would trouble you if disclosed to you. But if you<a class=""sup""><sup>pl </sup></a>ask about them while the Recital{1}is being <span class=""h"">bestowed from on high<sup foot_note=""79956"" class=""qiraat"">2</sup> </span>, they will be disclosed to you; Allah has pardoned that, for Allah is Oft-Forgiving, Clement.",footnotes:1:The Arabic word used is Qur’an which literally means ‘recital’ or ‘recitation’.
  5,102,"Surely, some people before you asked<i class=""s"">(about) </i>them, then of them they became deniers."
  5,103,"Never did Allah institute<i class=""s"">(the superstitions of) </i>: the ear-slit she-camel or the free-grazing she-camel or the successive female-bearing cattle or the protected ten-sire camel. But those who denied fabricate lies against Allah, and most of them do not reason."
